    <releaseNotes>
      RunLog 3.0.0 Release Notes

      Major Changes:
      * Restructured library into multiple files for better organization
      * Added dependency on AaTurpin.Utilities package
      * Changed from ILogEventSink interface to concrete sink types
      * File sinks are now buffered by default for better performance
      * Added thread-safety via synchronization locks

      New Features:
      * Enhanced error handling with retry logic for IO issues
      * Added fallback logging location when primary destination fails
      * Extended support for format specifiers in log templates
      * Improved file path handling with PathUtils
      * Better DateTime handling for rolling intervals
      * Public Sinks property on Logger class for inspection

      Bug Fixes:
      * Fixed issues with concurrent access to shared resources
      * Improved message rendering with robust regex pattern matching
      * Better handling of buffered writes with proper cleanup

      Performance Improvements:
      * Buffered file operations by default for higher throughput
      * More efficient message queue processing
      * Improved file rolling logic
    </releaseNotes>
